To compute the LIX readability score, we will use the following formula:

LIX = (antal ord / antal meningar) + (antal ord > 1 syllab / totalt antal ord) * 100 + antal meningar / (antal ord) * 100

Where:
- antal ord = total number of words
- antal meningar = total number of sentences
- antal ord > 1 syllab = total number of words with more than 1 syllable

Breaking down the text:

- antal ord (total number of words) = 54
- antal meningar (total number of sentences) = 5
- antal ord > 1 syllab (total number of words with more than 1 syllable) = 
    Here we need to manually count the words with more than 1 syllable:
    1. starkt, flöde, gångtrafikanter, flesta, t-bane, uppgången, Hornsbruksgatan, Högalidsparken, funktionera, starka, övergång, bergsvägg, fusion, byggnadstypologi, topografi = 14
- antal ord > 1 syllab = 14

Now we can compute the LIX score:

(antal ord / antal meningar) = 54 / 5 = 10.8
(antal ord > 1 syllab / totalt antal ord) * 100 = (14 / 54) * 100 = 25.93
antal meningar / (antal ord) * 100 = (5 / 54) * 100 = 9.26

LIX = 10.8 + 25.93 + 9.26 * 0.1 (only the decimal part for the third term is included) 
LIX ≈ 10.8 + 25.93 + 0.93
LIX  ≈ 37.66, rounded to 38

LIX= 38